Miss Rivers, Nyekachi Douglas, has won the Most Beautiful Girl in Nigeria (MBGN) 2019 crown. The contest took place at the Gabriel Okara Cultural Centre in Bayelsa State on Friday. Miss Nyekachi defeated 36 other contestants to become the most beautiful girl in Nigeria. Douglas is to get a brand new car and other mouthwatering prizes as the winner. She will also represent Nigeria at the Miss World 2019 pageantry, which will be held on December 14, at the ExCeL London in London. This year’s being the 32nd edition, was themed as “Every Woman.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.